div.p:
Sir: I have the honor to refer to the Embassy’s telegrams Nos. 435, August 25, noon; Vol. iii, p. 53. 437, August 25, 7 p.m.;
Ibid., p. 54. 440, August 26, 2 p.m.;
Ibid., p. 55. 442, August 28, 11 a.m.;Not printed. 445, August 28, 10 p.m.; 447, August 30, 9 a.m.;Telegram No. 447 not printed. and subsequent telegrams in regard to the fall of the Hiranuma Cabinet and the formation of a new Cabinet under General Nobuyuki Abe.
